{"title": "Color of a Great City", "description": "Theodore Dreiser was highly acclaimed for his novels and other writing. This non-fiction work takes place in many areas of New York City in the early 20th Century. Dreiser writes of lives packed into cramped tenements, of the likely end, but perhaps not, of an affair, of those who guided ships through turbulent waters, and of life in a home for retired seamen. We're taken to the new subways where track workers risked deadly accidents as they struggled to earn a living. Animal slaughter, the glory and heartbreak of song-writing, the shabby \"sandwich man\", deadly jealousy in Little Italy, and much more is vividly brought to life by this brilliant author. (Summary by Lee Smalley)", "duration": 30944, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2227", "name": "Theodore Dreiser"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/color_great_city_ls_2210_librivox/colorofagreatcity_2210.jpg", "copyright_year": "1923", "genres": ["Art", "Design & Architecture", "Essays & Short Works"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Lee Smalley"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Lee Smalley"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Ann Boulais"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Foreword", "readers": [8138], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/color_great_city_ls_2210_librivox/colorofagreatcity_00_dreiser_64kb.mp3", "duration": 774}, {"section": 1, "title": "The City of My Dreams", "readers": [8138], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/color_great_city_ls_2210_librivox/colorofagreatcity_01_dreiser_64kb.mp3", "duration": 489}, {"section": 2, "title": "The City Awakes", "readers": [8138], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/color_great_city_ls_2210_librivox/colorofagreatcity_02_dreiser_64kb.mp3", "duration": 359}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Waterfront", "readers": [8138], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/color_great_city_ls_2210_librivox/colorof